# Scratch synth test wavs. (tts/voices/*.onnx ARE committed, via Git LFS.)
tts/_*.wav

# Parser training tooling lives on the `stt` branch only, never on `main`. This
# guard (kept on main, intentionally absent on stt so new training files there
# still track without -f) stops the leftover training data/scripts from being
# re-committed to main by a stray `git add`. NOTE: a merge from stt still brings
# the dir in as tracked files -> run `git rm -r dsl_parser_training` after merging.
dsl_parser_training/
